2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of energy detection based spectrum sensing, which is a key component of cognitive radio networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the behavior of energy detection based spectrum sensing over enriched fading conditions, which can be considered as a system with uncertain parameters. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper may be relevant to the design of multiagent systems that utilize spectrum sensing for communication and coordination.
